Fig. 5
I–J). Abdominal neuropodia with two series of brown points. Abdominal neurochaetae and uncini translucent (
Fig. 5K
). Caudal peduncle yellowish to translucent toward distal part, basal region with lateral brown points.

Parathorax
. Three parathoracic segments (
Fig. 5A
). Chaetigers with a pair of branchiae. Notopodia with lanceolate chaetae interspersed with long capillary chaetae (
Fig. 5I
). Neuropodia with lanceolate chaetae interspersed with small lanceolate chaetae (
Fig. 5J
); neurochaetae thinner than notochaetae.
